Key Match Events: Lionel Mpasi stepped up to send Congo into the quarterfinals
Mohamed Bayo scored in the eighth minute of stoppage time to send Guinea into the quarterfinals
Mohamed Abou Gabal struck the crossbar with his spot kick
Mostafa Mohamed equalized from the spot in first-half stoppage time
Post-Match Reflections: Guinea coach Kaba Diawara expressed pride in the team's achievement
Mohamed Salah's absence due to injury
Miscellaneous Highlights: Egypt goalkeeper Mohamed Abou Gabal played because Mohamed El Shenawy dislocated his shoulder
Equatorial Guinea defender Federico Bikoro was shown a straight red card in the 55th for kicking Bayo while attempting a clearance
